# Quick Reference: Java 17 Migration Changes

## Package Imports to Update in Future Code

If you're writing new code or modifying existing code, use these Jakarta EE packages instead of the old javax packages:

### Annotations
```java
// OLD (javax)
import javax.annotation.PostConstruct;
import javax.annotation.PreDestroy;
import javax.annotation.Nullable;

// NEW (jakarta)
import jakarta.annotation.PostConstruct;
import jakarta.annotation.PreDestroy;
import jakarta.annotation.Nullable;
```

### Persistence (JPA)
```java
// OLD (javax)
import javax.persistence.Entity;
import javax.persistence.Table;
import javax.persistence.Id;
import javax.persistence.GeneratedValue;
import javax.persistence.Column;
import javax.persistence.EntityManager;

// NEW (jakarta)
import jakarta.persistence.Entity;
import jakarta.persistence.Table;
import jakarta.persistence.Id;
import jakarta.persistence.GeneratedValue;
import jakarta.persistence.Column;
import jakarta.persistence.EntityManager;
```

### Validation
```java
// OLD (javax)
import javax.validation.constraints.NotNull;
import javax.validation.constraints.Size;

// NEW (jakarta)
import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotNull;
import jakarta.validation.constraints.Size;
```

## Failsafe API Changes (v2.x to v3.x)

### Retry Policy
```java
// OLD (Failsafe 2.x with net.jodah)
import net.jodah.failsafe.Failsafe;
import net.jodah.failsafe.RetryPolicy;
import java.time.temporal.ChronoUnit;

RetryPolicy<T> policy = new RetryPolicy<T>()
    .withBackoff(1L, 30L, ChronoUnit.SECONDS)
    .withMaxRetries(-1);

// NEW (Failsafe 3.x with dev.failsafe)
import dev.failsafe.Failsafe;
import dev.failsafe.RetryPolicy;
import java.time.Duration;

RetryPolicy<T> policy = RetryPolicy.<T>builder()
    .withBackoff(Duration.ofSeconds(1), Duration.ofSeconds(30))
    .withMaxRetries(-1)
    .build();
```

## Spring Boot 3.x Changes

### SpringDoc OpenAPI
```xml
<!-- OLD -->
<dependency>
    <groupId>org.springdoc</groupId>
    <artifactId>springdoc-openapi-ui</artifactId>
</dependency>

<!-- NEW -->
<dependency>
    <groupId>org.springdoc</groupId>
    <artifactId>springdoc-openapi-starter-webmvc-ui</artifactId>
</dependency>
```

## Build Commands

### Standard Build
```bash
mvn clean verify
```

### Quick Compile (Skip Tests)
```bash
mvn clean compile -DskipTests
```

### Full Build with All Tests
```bash
mvn clean verify -P full
```

## Verification Checklist

After making code changes:
- [ ] No compilation errors
- [ ] All unit tests pass
- [ ] No deprecation warnings (or they are documented)
- [ ] Application starts successfully
- [ ] Database operations work correctly
- [ ] Web services respond properly
- [ ] WebSocket connections establish correctly

## Common Issues and Solutions

### Issue: Cannot find javax.* classes
**Solution**: Replace with jakarta.* equivalent

### Issue: RetryPolicy cannot be instantiated
**Solution**: Use the builder pattern with RetryPolicy.builder()

### Issue: Spring Boot incompatibilities
**Solution**: Ensure you're using Spring Boot 3.3.4 or later

### Issue: WebClient SSL errors
**Solution**: Verify SSL configuration is compatible with Spring Boot 3.x

## Java 17 Features You Can Now Use

- **Text Blocks** (Java 13+)
  ```java
  String json = """
      {
        "key": "value"
      }
      """;
  ```

- **Pattern Matching for instanceof** (Java 16+)
  ```java
  if (obj instanceof String s) {
      System.out.println(s.toLowerCase());
  }
  ```

- **Records** (Java 16+)
  ```java
  public record Point(int x, int y) {}
  ```

- **Sealed Classes** (Java 17)
  ```java
  public sealed class Shape permits Circle, Rectangle {}
  ```

- **Switch Expressions** (Java 14+)
  ```java
  String result = switch (day) {
      case MONDAY, FRIDAY -> "Working";
      case SATURDAY, SUNDAY -> "Weekend";
      default -> "Midweek";
  };
  ```
